The paper deals with quantum information set decoding algorithms for binary linear codes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The algorithms involve analyzing and manipulating graphs, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses techniques for similarity search, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM).
